metadata.name: Head In The Clouds
metadata.description:
Head In The Clouds

Take some inspiration while you’re up there. 

Image dimensions - 4096x4096

A collaborative piece created by two yellow worlds. 

The yellow dress concept and writing by Sarah Lyndsay 

Art work by Ada Crow   

Artists 

Ada Crow  - Art Historian | Artist AI & photographer

Inspired by movements such as surrealism, Dadaism, Flemish painting and baroque, I work the image in a way in which the aesthetic is no less important than the concept itself with which I play.

Sarah Lyndsay - Photographer | Storyteller | Artist 

A passionate self-portrait photographer who combined her love for all genres to create ethereal images while wearing beautiful, flowing gowns.  Her work evokes emotion through her storytelling which mirrors her own personal development journey through life.  The yellow dress is her iconic look and she travels the world with these dresses packed in her camera bag, photographing herself in surreal landscapes.  She uses a long exposure technique when creating her images which helps her stand out from the crowd and is often found with her head always in the clouds.
